exports[`format snapshots > matches triage markdown snapshot 1`] = `
"# Example Paper

## Triage Card

**One-Line Thesis**  
The paper argues that cue tokens explain most of the observed effect.

**Contribution Type**  
negative result/falsification, new method

**Mechanism Decomposition**
- **Bias / Method:** Sparse methods prefer simple repeated signals.
- **Data / Structure:** Cue tokens are easier to isolate than distributed reasoning traces.
- **Claimed Effect:** Candidate reasoning features fire on cues instead of reasoning.
- **Why Authors Expect It:** Simple repeated signals are easier to capture than messy latent structure.

**Strongest Evidence**  
Cue injection recreates many reported feature activations.

> Injecting cue tokens activates many candidate features.

**Weakest Link**  
Only small models are evaluated.

> We only evaluate small models.

**Investment Recommendation**  
**Read Now** — Worth reading if you work on interpretability.
"
`;

